TITLE: Defining Wrapper Type Structure for Open Next.js Backends
DESCRIPTION: Defines the type structure for wrappers, which are the main entry points for Open Next.js backends. Includes the WrapperHandler type and the Wrapper type that extends BaseOverride.
SOURCE: https://github.com/opennextjs/docs/blob/main/pages/aws/inner_workings/components/overview.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
type WrapperHandler<
  E extends BaseEventOrResult = InternalEvent,
  R extends BaseEventOrResult = InternalResult,
> = (handler: OpenNextHandler<E, R>, converter: Converter<E, R>) => Promise<(...args: any[]) => any>;

export type Wrapper<
  E extends BaseEventOrResult = InternalEvent,
  R extends BaseEventOrResult = InternalResult,
> = BaseOverride & {
  wrapper: WrapperHandler<E, R>;
  supportStreaming: boolean;
};
```

