TITLE: Accessing Cloudflare KV Binding in Next.js Route Handler
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use getCloudflareContext() to access a KV namespace binding in a Next.js route handler. This example shows how to put a value into KV and then retrieve it for the response.
SOURCE: https://github.com/opennextjs/docs/blob/main/pages/cloudflare/former-releases/0.6/bindings.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { getCloudflareContext } from "@opennextjs/cloudflare";

export async function GET(request) {
  let responseText = "Hello World";

  const myKv = getCloudflareContext().env.MY_KV_NAMESPACE;
  await myKv.put("foo", "bar");
  const foo = await myKv.get("foo");

  return new Response(foo);
}
```

